data.name: Amazon S3
data.description: View of key metrics relating to the health and performance of the Amazon S3

markdown.markdownText:
**Amazon S3**
![Amazon S3](https://icon.icepanel.io/AWS/svg/Storage/Simple-Storage-Service.svg)
Amazon S3 is an object storage service that offers scalability, data availability, security, and performance. Store and protect any amount of data for a range of use cases, such as data lakes, websites, cloud-native applications, backups, archive, machine learning, and analytics.

This dashboard is part of the out-of-box Amazon S3 extension providing visibility to and alerting on key performance metrics.

**Details of integrations to bring in Amazon S3 logs** [here](https://coralogix.com/docs/cloudwatch-metricstreams-kinesis-data-firehose/)

**Use Cases Covered** * Number of Objects (total number of objects stored in a general purpose Amazon S3 bucket for all storage classes) * Bucket Size (total amount of data in bytes stored in a Amazon S3 bucket) * All Requests (total number of HTTP requests made to a Amazon S3 bucket, regardless of type) * GET Requests (number of HTTP GET requests made for objects in a Amazon S3 bucket) * PUT Requests (number of HTTP PUT requests made for objects in a Amazon S3 bucket) * DELETE Requests (number of HTTP DELETE requests made for objects in a Amazon S3 bucket * POST Requests (number of HTTP POST requests made to a Amazon S3 bucket) * LIST Requests (number of HTTP requests that LIST the contents of a bucket) * Bytes Downloaded (number of bytes downloaded for requests made to an Amazon S3 bucket, where the response includes a body) * Bytes Uploaded (number of bytes uploaded for requests made to an Amazon S3 bucket, where the request includes a body) * **4xxErrors** (number of HTTP 4xx client error status code requests made to an Amazon S3 bucket with a value of either 0 or 1) * **5xxErrors** (number of HTTP 5xx server error status code requests made to an Amazon S3 bucket with a value of either 0 or 1) * **First Byte Latency** (per-request time from the complete request being received by an Amazon S3 bucket to when the response starts to be returned). * **Total Request Latency** (elapsed per-request time from the first byte received to the last byte sent to an Amazon S3 bucket) More about performance monitoring of Amazon S3[ here](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/metrics-dimensions.html)
